HEADWORD: Betacismus
<hw>Be`ta*cis"mus</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Excessive or extended use of
the <it>b</it> sound in speech, due to conversion of other sounds into
it, as through inability to distinguish them from <it>b</it>, or because
of difficulty in pronouncing them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Betaine</ent>⟦br⟧
